  rdfs:label "updated via" ; gb:description """Cost model updates go through Protocol Parameter Change governance: the Plutus team benchmarks builtins, fits cost functions via R scripts, and the new coefficients are submitted as a governance action requiring CC 2/3 and DRep 67% (Technical group threshold).""" ;
  gb:edgeIndex 72 ; dcterms:isPartOf <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-knowledge-maps/rdf> .

n:treasury-budgeting cardano:constrains n:action-treasury .
n:treasury-budgeting gbedge:gates n:action-treasury .
e:73 a gb:EdgeAssertion ;
  gb:from n:treasury-budgeting ; gb:to n:action-treasury ; gb:predicate gbedge:gates ;
  rdfs:label "gates" ; gb:description """Treasury Withdrawals can only be submitted after a Net Change Limit and Budget have been approved. The Net Change Limit (Info Action, DRep 50% + CC 2/3) sets the maximum withdrawal amount per period. Budget proposals (also Info Actions, DRep 50% + CC 2/3) allocate portions of that limit. Only then can Treasury Withdrawal governance actions be submitted against the approved budget.""" ;
  gb:edgeIndex 73 ; dcterms:isPartOf <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-knowledge-maps/rdf> .

n:action-info prov:used n:treasury-budgeting .
n:action-info gbedge:used%20for n:treasury-budgeting .
e:74 a gb:EdgeAssertion ;
  gb:from n:action-info ; gb:to n:treasury-budgeting ; gb:predicate gbedge:used%20for ;
  rdfs:label "used for" ; gb:description """Info Actions, despite having no direct on-chain effect, are the mechanism for the treasury budgeting process. Net Change Limits and Budget approvals are submitted as Info Actions with effective voting thresholds of DRep 50% + CC 2/3. This repurposes the Info Action type for binding community decisions that gate subsequent Treasury Withdrawals.""" ;
  gb:edgeIndex 74 ; dcterms:isPartOf <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-knowledge-maps/rdf> .

n:param-exceptions cardano:modifiesVotingFor n:param-group-governance .
n:param-exceptions gbedge:overrides%20thresholds%20from n:param-group-governance .
e:75 a gb:EdgeAssertion ;
  gb:from n:param-exceptions ; gb:to n:param-group-governance ; gb:predicate gbedge:overrides%20thresholds%20from ;
  rdfs:label "overrides thresholds from" ; gb:description """Some parameters that belong to the Economic or Technical groups are constitutionally elevated to Governance group thresholds (DRep 75% + CC 2/3). This includes dRepDeposit, stakePoolDeposit, stakeAddressDeposit, minPoolCost, and committeeMinSize. The Constitution treats these as governance-critical despite their technical classification.""" ;
  gb:edgeIndex 75 ; dcterms:isPartOf <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-knowledge-maps/rdf> .

n:param-exceptions cardano:modifiesVotingFor n:action-param-change .
n:param-exceptions gbedge:modifies%20voting%20for n:action-param-change .
e:76 a gb:EdgeAssertion ;
  gb:from n:param-exceptions ; gb:to n:action-param-change ; gb:predicate gbedge:modifies%20voting%20for ;
  rdfs:label "modifies voting for" ; gb:description """Per-parameter threshold exceptions change which bodies vote and at what thresholds for specific parameter changes. For example, committeeMaxTermLength only requires DRep 67% with no CC or SPO vote — a unique exception where the CC is excluded because the parameter directly governs CC member terms, and self-governance would be a conflict of interest.""" ;
  gb:edgeIndex 76 ; dcterms:isPartOf <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-knowledge-maps/rdf> .

